      <h1 class='title'>Regulatory Impact Assessments</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 20 November 2002 vol 394 c37WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_37ws' title='Col. 37WS &mdash; HC Deb 20 November 2002 vol 394 c37WS' name='column_37ws' href='#column_37ws' rel='bookmark'>37WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0394P0_20021120_CWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-douglas-alexander' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0394P0_20021120_CWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Mr Douglas Alexander' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-douglas-alexander" title="Mr Douglas Alexander">The Minister of State, Cabinet Office (Mr. Douglas Alexander)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Government is committed to ensuring that regulations are necessary, give effective protection, balance cost and risk, are fair and command public confidence. In accordance with this, we require Departments to produce and publish RIAs for all regulatory proposals likely to have an impact on business.</p><p>I have today presented to Parliament a Command Paper listing RIAs published between 1st January and 30th June 2002. Copies of those listed have been placed in the libraries of both Houses. This is the seventeenth such Command Paper</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
